<P><H1 align=center>DC131 – ADD/EDIT ARREARS HISTORY</H1>
<P></P>
<P><FONT color=red><STRONG>NOTE: </STRONG>fields shown in 
red are mandatory and must be completed to proceed</FONT>            </P>
<P><H3>Applicant: </H3>Select the applicant who has previously 
been in arrears, this will be pre-completed if the application is in sole names.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Maximum arrears balance: </H3>Input the maximum amount 
of arrears that has existed.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Monthly repayment: </H3>Input the amount of any monthly 
payment that has been imposed to clear the arrears.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Description of Loan: </H3>Select the type of loan that 
has been/is in arrears from the drop down list.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Mortgage Account in Arrears: </H3>If Mortgage is 
selected from the previous drop down list, this field will be active. Select the 
mortgage that has been in arrears from the drop down list, this list will be 
populated from a previous application question regarding current/previous 
mortgage accounts.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Maximum number of months in arrears: </H3>Input the 
maximum number of months the applicant has been in arrears.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Date cleared: </H3>Input the date that the arrears were 
cleared.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Other details: </H3>Such as arrangements/agreements 
regarding the arrears, that have been agreed with the other lender.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Are there any additional arrears holders: </H3>Note the 
details of any other occupant of the property who had arrears.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Another: </H3>click the ‘Another’ button if further 
instances of arrears need to be noted, and complete the above fields again.
<P></P>
<P><H3>OK: </H3>click ‘OK’ when all completed, which will lead 
back to the previous screen.
<P></P>
